                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00118 European War (1939)/1885: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-19T19:30:00-04:00"
                            >May 19, 1943—7:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–29. Your 240, March 26. Osmun Group, now made up of Colonel Osmun, Lieutenant
                    Colonel Graybeal, Lieutenant Colonel Lash, and Major Charles S. Cutting,
                    assigned Military Observers with Personal rank of Military Attaché and Assistant
                    Military Attachés to Mission at New Delhi. Advise appropriate authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
